## ðŸ”¹ LINE 1

### `bash /root/curl-test.sh`

### ðŸ” Matlab kya hai?

* `bash` â†’ bol raha hai **Bash shell se script chalao**
* `/root/curl-test.sh` â†’ ye **script ka full path** hai

### ðŸ§  Ye script karta kya hai?

Ye script:

* baar-baar web application ko request bhejta hai
* jaise browser refresh karna repeatedly

Example:

```bash
curl http://webapp-service
```

ye kaam loop me karta hai.

### â“ Kyun chalate hain?

ðŸ‘‰ **Check karne ke liye**:

* app chal rahi hai ya nahi
* update ke time down ho rahi hai ya nahi

---

## ðŸ”¹ LINE 2 (Actual magic yahin hota hai)

```bash
kubectl set image deployment/webapp webapp=kodekloud/webapp-color:v2
```

### ðŸ” Word by word samjho:

| Part                        | Matlab                             |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `kubectl`                   | Kubernetes ko command dene ka tool |
| `set image`                 | container ka image change karo     |
| `deployment/webapp`         | deployment ka naam = **webapp**    |
| `webapp=`                   | container ka naam                  |
| `kodekloud/webapp-color:v2` | **new version image**              |

### ðŸ§  Simple language:

> â€œO Kubernetes, webapp deployment ke container ka image **version v2** kar deâ€

---

### â“ Isse kya hota hai?

* Kubernetes **naye pods banata hai**
* purane pods **ek-ek karke** band karta hai
* users ko **koi downtime nahi milta**

Isko hi bolte hain ðŸ‘‰ **Rolling Update**

---

## ðŸ”¹ LINE 3

```bash
kubectl rollout status deployment/webapp
```

### ðŸ” Matlab?

* `rollout` â†’ deployment update process
* `status` â†’ abhi kya chal raha hai check karo
* `deployment/webapp` â†’ webapp deployment ka status

### ðŸ§  Output kya aata hai?

```text
deployment "webapp" successfully rolled out
```

### â“ Kyun use karte hain?

ðŸ‘‰ Confirm karne ke liye:

* update complete hua ya nahi
* koi error to nahi aaya

---

## ðŸ”¹ FULL COMMAND WITH `&&` (IMPORTANT)

```bash
bash /root/curl-test.sh \
&& kubectl set image deployment/webapp webapp=kodekloud/webapp-color:v2 \
&& kubectl rollout status deployment/webapp
```

### ðŸ§  `&&` ka simple rule:

> **Agar pehla command successful â†’ tabhi next chalega**

### Flow:

1ï¸âƒ£ curl script start
2ï¸âƒ£ image update hota hai
3ï¸âƒ£ rollout status check hota hai

---

## ðŸ”¥ REAL LIFE EXAMPLE (100% CLEAR)

Soch:

* `curl-test.sh` = customer website refresh kar raha
* `set image` = backend update chal raha
* `rollout status` = manager check kar raha â€œdeploy hua ya nahiâ€

Customers ko **website band nahi dikhti**
âž¡ï¸ ye hi DevOps ka kaam hai

---

## ðŸ§  ONE-LINE CDAC ANSWER

> curl-test.sh application availability test karta hai, kubectl set image rolling update perform karta hai aur rollout status update completion verify karta hai.

---

## ðŸŽ¯ INTERVIEW SHORT ANSWER

**Q:** Why do we run curl-test.sh during rollout?
**A:** To verify that application remains accessible during rolling updates.

